{
  "stem": "24814.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "James Episcopal Cathedral, where a nice old lady used to give me Scotch bread.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but to keep my mother, sister, and the others happy, I would pro forma go to the Catholic school, so I'm kind of an expert on theology in a couple of lines.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, lots, because we lived, first on the near-- the middle north side of Chicago, Albany, Ravenswood area.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were many, many of the Jews who had left Russia in the pogroms had settled there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I remember seeing the Hebrew letters on stores.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was on Montrose Avenue, and that part of Chicago.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And many of my playmates were Jewish boys.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- some of my father's closest friends were Jews who were in the medical publishing, [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Mal ?] [? and Jay ?] [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Herz ?] of Minneapolis, and others.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so I remember sitting around our huge dining room table with the silver and the crystal, and long discussions of the theater and books and letters.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That's when I-- I was teasing some Jewish friends of mine not long ago, said you can't be Jewish and be conservative, sorry.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Jewish means humanistic, cultured, progressive, forward-looking, liberal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] That's what it was around our house anyway.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was some mindless anti-Semitism, I think, among little boys.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They didn't know what they were saying.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They'd yell, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], just as a war cry as they ran down the street, throwing rocks at each other.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they didn't know what the words meant, but they'd heard them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Beyond that, I don't think there was anything very vocal or deliberate or organized.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just the Democratic Party, to the great discomfort of my father, who thought that anyone who was a New Deal Roosevelt Democrat was right on the skirts of Moscow or something.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
